<doc id="1078452" wikidata="Q14950422" url="?curid=1078452" title="Wes Hamilton">
<text>Wes Hamilton (born April 24, 1953) is a former American football offensive lineman who was drafted by the Minnesota Vikings in the 3rd round in the 1976 NFL draft. He played college football at the University of Tulsa. One of Wes&#x27;s sons, Ben Hamilton, was an offensive lineman who played for the Seattle Seahawks. His life after football includes his successful career as a small business owner of an Allegra Marketing, Print &amp; Mail franchise in the Minneapolis suburbs. He resides nearby with his college sweetheart, Linda. He is active in his church and is involved with charitable work.

