<doc id="1078710" wikidata="Q1953052" url="?curid=1078710" title="Bill Gates' flower fly">
<text>Bill Gates&#x27; flower fly (&quot;Eristalis gatesi&quot;) is a flower fly endemic to Costa Rica named after Bill Gates. Another fly found in similar habitats was named after Gates&#x27; associate Paul Allen, called Paul Allen&#x27;s flower fly (&quot;Eristalis alleni&quot;); according to Chris Thompson, the describer of these species, both names were in &quot;recognition of [their] great contributions to the science of Dipterology&quot;.

==See also==

* List of organisms named after famous people (born 1950–present)

